# Supabase — Complete RAG Pipeline Reference

RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) = let an LLM answer questions using YOUR data.
The pipeline: chunk documents → embed chunks → store in pgvector → retrieve relevant chunks → build prompt → generate answer → stream to user.

---

## Schema: Documents + Sections (NOT one flat table)

```sql
-- Parent: one row per source document
CREATE TABLE documents (
  id          BIGINT PRIMARY KEY GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY,
  name        TEXT NOT NULL,
  storage_object_id UUID REFERENCES storage.objects(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  created_by  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Child: one row per chunk — this is what gets embedded
CREATE TABLE document_sections (
  id          BIGINT PRIMARY KEY GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY,
  document_id BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES documents(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  content     TEXT NOT NULL,
  embedding   VECTOR(1536),        -- OpenAI text-embedding-3-small dimensions
  token_count INT,                 -- track token usage
  created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Enable RLS on BOTH tables
ALTER TABLE documents ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE document_sections ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- HNSW index for fast similarity search
CREATE INDEX ON document_sections USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops);
```

